parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to bounce uncontrollably, making it difficult to steer and control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: the air suspension stops working in cold weather
the vehicle drops to the ground
the running boards are rusty and bolts come loose
and the traction control system does not work when the suspension is out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the running boards can cause them to break off while driving, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

the aluminum piece that holds the running boards to the vehicle breaks off
and the running boards slide out while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel pump and computer module can cause engine stalling and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Engine failure can cause fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while driving at high speeds.

The failure of the fuel system can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to difficulties in determining the fuel level, which can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the stability control system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
The sudden stalling of the engine and activation of fail-safe mode can cause loss of power and control, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds.
